  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6597.12 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-23.4B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+23.5B), dealers are currently in buy mode as spot trades above the negative gamma strike, creating upward pressure toward the 6605 resistance wall. The breakout regime with -21.1B total GEX means dealers will aggressively buy this push higher, but expect violent rejection if we hit that 6605 wall where they flip to heavy selling. Key battle zone is 6590-6605 with massive opposing gamma forces creating a tight amplification corridor—any break below 6590 triggers dealer selling cascade, while sustained move above 6605 faces immediate dealer resistance.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent whipsaw action between 6590-6605 until one side breaks definitively.",
